{"key":"processedPost-10754126","value":{"id":10754126,"first":10753080,"last":10755075,"when":1248791500,"utime":"07/28/09 05:31 PM","cleanedPost":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><strong>avorg said:</strong><br />the setup should work alright.<br />rule of thumb is if you can see the mycelium, there is enough light.</blockquote><br />I wonder how much longer we're going to keep hearing that?&nbsp; It's not a rule of thumb, it's flat out wrong.&nbsp; Mushrooms <i>derive energy</i> from light, and bright light will produce more mushrooms, bigger and meatier mushrooms with fatter caps and much more weight.<br />I'd get your tub out of that closet.&nbsp; You want circulating air around the tub and very bright light.&nbsp; Put it near a window, but avoid direct sunlight for more than a few minutes a day.&nbsp; If you don't have a suitable window, use a bright fluorescent lamp.<br />RR"}}